The Board and Management of NetOne Cellular (Private) Limited regret to advisethat on 30 April 2022 at around 09:00 hours, one of the employees of NetOne whowas a Technician was involved in a tragic incident at Chilonga Bridge, along RundeRiver in Chiredzi. The company vehicle that he was driving, a Land Rover Defenderwas swept off the bridge as he attempted to cross Runde River. The local communitymembers who were present at the time of the incident acted promptly and alerted theZimbabwe Republic Police and NetOne of the unfortunate incident. The companyâ€™semergency procedures were immediately activated. On the same day the NetOne Chief Executive Officer and members of the NetOneteam travelled to Chiredzi where they immediately got in touch with the ZimbabweRepublic Police. Due to the strength of the water current, it was not possible for therescue team to reach the vehicle. On Sunday 1 May 2022, the Zimbabwe RepublicPolice Sub Aqua Unit began the rescue operation. Unfortunately their efforts werefutile as they were working against a strong water current. Following an assessmentof the area where the vehicle was, it was established that more resources wererequired for the operation to be successful. NetOne Cellular (Private) Limited, together with the local community, the ZimbabweRepublic Police and its Sub-Aqua unit, Malilangwe Trust, Tongaat Hulett, theDepartment of Civil Protection and the Member of Parliament for Chiredzi SouthConstituency, Honourable Killion Callisto Gwanetsa, worked together to mobilise thenecessary resources for the operation.The rescue operation resumed on Monday 2 May 2022 leading to the recovery of theremains of NetOne staff member Mr. Samson Zvarimwa, together with a yet-to-beidentified passenger from the vehicle. The NetOne Board, Management and Staff thank the Chilonga community and thelocal leadership for their support and remarkable efforts in the recovery operation. We would also like to thank the Zimbabwe Republic Police and its Sub-Aqua unit,Malilangwe Trust, Tongaat Hulett, the Department of Civil Protection, HonourableKillion Callisto Gwanetsa MP for the assistance rendered. We extend our heartfelt condolences to the families of the deceased during thisdifficult time. Mr. Samson Zvarimwa has been a valued member of the NetOne teamsince 1 July 2011 and will be sorely missed. Our thoughts and prayers are with thefamily, friends and colleagues of the departed. May their souls rest in peace.